💻 System Requirements

Before running this project, ensure your computer meets the following requirements:

Operating System

- Windows 10 or Windows 11

Software Requirements

- Visual Studio 2022 (Community, Professional, or Enterprise)
- .NET Desktop Development workload installed
- .NET Framework 4.8 or later (or the framework version used by the project)

Recommended Hardware

- Processor: Intel Core i3 or AMD Ryzen 3 (or better)
- RAM: Minimum 4 GB (8 GB recommended)
- Storage: At least 500 MB of free disk space

---

📥 Installation Guide

Step 1: Install Visual Studio 2022

Download and install Visual Studio 2022 from Microsoft's official website.

During installation, select the following workload:

- ✅ .NET Desktop Development

This workload installs everything required to build and run WPF applications.

---

Step 2: Clone or Download the Project

Clone the repository using Git:

git clone https://github.com/yourusername/Tyrone-Cybersecurity-Awareness-AI-Chatbot.git

Or download the project as a ZIP file and extract it.

---

Step 3: Open the Project

1. Launch Visual Studio 2022.
2. Select Open a project or solution.
3. Navigate to the project folder.
4. Open the ".sln" (Solution) file.

---

Step 4: Restore Dependencies

If prompted, allow Visual Studio to restore any required NuGet packages.

---

Step 5: Build the Project

From the menu:

Build → Build Solution

Or press:

Ctrl + Shift + B

Ensure the build completes successfully with no errors.

---

Step 6: Run the Application

Press:

F5

or click the Start button.

The application will launch, allowing you to:

- Chat with the Cybersecurity AI Assistant
- Complete cybersecurity quizzes
- Manage task reminders
- View the activity log

---

📦 Compiler & Development Environment

- IDE: Visual Studio 2022
- Language: C#
- UI Framework: Windows Presentation Foundation (WPF)
- UI Markup: XAML
- Compiler: Microsoft C# Compiler (Roslyn)
- Build System: MSBuild
- Runtime: .NET Framework

---

⚠️ Troubleshooting

If the project does not run:

- Verify that the .NET Desktop Development workload is installed.
- Ensure the correct .NET Framework version is available.
- Restore NuGet packages.
- Clean the solution (Build → Clean Solution) and rebuild (Build → Rebuild Solution).
- Make sure the project is set as the Startup Project before pressing F5.